# The backlog CSVs are exported from the authoritative backlog xlsx and use
# RFC 4180 CRLF line endings — uniformly, in all four files. Keep them
# byte-for-byte as exported: no end-of-line normalization, and a CR at end of
# line is not a whitespace error (re-review finding 4: `git diff --check`
# flagged every edited row).
docs/backlog/*.csv -text whitespace=cr-at-eol

# The cross-model review requests embed unified diffs verbatim. In diff format a
# context line is prefixed with a space, so a blank source line becomes a line
# containing exactly one space — `git diff --check` reads those as trailing
# whitespace (round-2 finding 8). Stripping them would corrupt the diff being
# reviewed, so the check is suppressed for these files instead.
GPT_REVIEW_REQUEST_*.md -whitespace

# The forecaster prompt is hashed over its raw bytes and that digest is pinned in
# tests/unit/test_prompt.py (D04 drift guard). Without an eol rule, a checkout with
# core.autocrlf=true can materialize CRLF in the worktree while the tree reads clean,
# changing the bytes the guard hashes and failing CI on an unmodified prompt. Force LF
# so every clean checkout receives the released bytes whose digest is pinned.
prompts/forecaster.md text eol=lf
